The paper deals with a problem of maintaining a conflict-free coloring for a set of intervals in $\mathbb{R}^1$ under insertions and deletions, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses trade-offs between the number of colors used and the number of intervals that are recolored, which is related to the area of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also presents results on the kinetic setting, which is related to the area of cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses upper and lower bounds for special cases, which is related to the area of cs.GR (Graphics).
